text: Amand Julien Solbach (10 May 1904 – 17 December 1967) was a French gymnast. He competed at the 1928 Summer Olympics and the 1936 Summer Olympics. He was married to two-time Olympian Jeanette Vogelbacher (1922–2018), who competed in 1948 and 1952. A gymnasium is named in his honour in Châteaudun, where he died in 1967. ==References== Category:1904 births Category:1967 deaths Category:French male artistic gymnasts Category:Olympic gymnasts of France Category:Gymnasts at the 1928 Summer Olympics Category:Gymnasts at the 1936 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Paris
